11:02 AM; Case called for Sentencing hearing.   Prosecuting attorney Alyssa M. Schaller in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Najuan L Brown in court, in custody at WCJ on OTP from Jackson Correctional Institution.  Attorney Daniel G. Mitchell in court for Najuan L Brown. Court notes a plea was taken back on 8/11/2022 and confirms with counsel they are prepared to proceed with sentencing today.  Defendant to be returned to Jackson Correctional Institution.  

Sentencing arguments made by the State.
Sentencing arguments made by Atty. Mitchell.
Ms. Terry, defendant's aunt, presents statements.
Defendant presents statements.

COUNT 2:
The Court Orders the Following:

2 Years & 6 Months Imprisonment (Consecutive to any other current sentence but Concurrent to Count 6)
-	1 Year of Initial Confinement
-	1 Year & 6 Months of Extended Supervision

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
-	Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
-	Follow any conditions deemed appropriate by Agent;
-	No contact with Victims, Business, and Co-Defendant listed in the Criminal Complaint.
-	AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-	Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s;
-	No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	No use or possession of any controlled substances without a valid doctor's prescription.

RESTITUTION: $349.00 to be paid to Kohls (resulting from Count 2); $361.76 to be paid to Walmart (resulting from Count 3), and $220.00 to be paid to Kohls (resulting from Count 5);

COSTS:  $278.00 (includes DRGOD surcharge);

DNA Surcharge: $250.00;

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid during term of imprisonment and during extended supervision. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.

Felony warnings, immigration warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.


